-- Hong Kong drawndown mortgage loans rise 7.7 pct in June from May
-- By Christina Lo
-- Fri Jul 25, 2014 06:20AM EDT
-- None



July 25 (Reuters) - New mortgage loans drawn down in Hong Kong totalled HK$17.6 billion ($2.27 billion) in June, up 7.7 percent from a month earlier, Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) data showed on Friday.

